CELL PHONES

v Parents will need to understand that
students will be allowed to call home and
receive calls only at certain times

¥ Throughout the tours students will be
directed to turn off phones and to put them
away

v Polite and good cell phone etiquette will be
required at all times

¥ Cell phone may be collected at night

¥ Cell phone usage at improper times (like text
messaging throughout the night) will be
considered a serious offense. This type of
behavior will result in the student being sent
home at parents’ expense.

v Family members and friends at home will
need to exhibit restraint and discipline when
calling someone on tour

v Chaperones will have their phones at all times